{
  "texts": [
    "The papers to be reviewed were classified for their analysis in accordance with the taxonomy presented in the following sub-sections, with which the decisions behind the experiences described in each study may be better understood.",
    "Immersive Virtual Reality (iVR) refers to the technology through which users feel fully immersed in the virtual world (Narasimha et al. 2019).",
    "It can also be defined as an extension of 3D-animation and static rendering (Bai 2022).",
    "iVR incorporates techniques that help users to feel their physical presence within the virtual environment (Won et al. 2023), and the interaction happens when the user moves or uses control devices in a natural and instinctive way (Feng et al. 2018).",
    "This review was therefore limited to academic papers published since 2015 and using iVR with HMDs."
  ]
}